ectual pursuit that still carries any reward.', 2414, 0), (467272, 'The price of every thing rises and falls from time to time and place to place and with every such change the purchasing power of money changes so far as that thing goes. ', 52683, 0), (467273, 'Stay on top of your finances. Don''t leave that up to others.', 71605, 0), (467274, 'I do not regard a broker as a member of the human race.', 143, 0), (467275, 'The only way you will ever permanently take control of your financial life is to dig deep and fix the root problem.', 10090, 0), (467276, 'Divorce is one of the most financially traumatic things you can go through. Money spent on getting mad or getting even is money wasted.', 4756, 0), (467277, 'We had a booming stock market in 1929 and then went into the world''s greatest depression. We have a booming stock market in 1999. Will the bubble somehow burst, and then we enter depression? Well, some things are not different.', 68748, 0), (467278, 'We teach about how to drive in school, but not how to manage finances.', 73901, 0), (467279, 'You only need to make one big score in finance to be a hero forever.', 73902, 0), (467280, 'When you print money, the money does not flow evenly into the economic system. It stays essentially in the financial service industry and among people that have access to these funds, mostly well-to-do people. It does not go to the worker.', 73903, 0), (467281, 'You don''t want to have so much money going toward your mortgage every month that you can''t enjoy life or take care of your other financial responsibilities.', 5846, 0), (467282, 'Landing a million-dollar investment for your startup is exhilarating. But as big as that number sounds, it doesn''t go far. Many startups just getting off the ground won''t have a CFO to monitor finances. It doesn''t take much for spending to spiral out of control.', 69457, 0), (467283, 'To be fair, lying is part and parcel of public life. Every politician has lied about something because they 