urity and credit rating, but for so long many did not know how to obtain one, or what to do with the information it provided.', 70459, 0), (467510, 'It''s cheaper to buy a house and finance it than it is to rent in many markets.', 73932, 0), (467511, 'We''ll have a public power authority, which will also have the ability to build power or finance power. And more importantly, we''ll have more power than our economy provides. All of that will give us leverage we don''t have today.', 73933, 0), (467512, 'In the deregulated realm of US banking and finance, crime does occasionally pay for its foul deeds, not in prison time but by making modest rebates to the victims.', 73934, 0), (467513, 'If US per capita income continues to grow at a rate of 1.5 percent a year, the country will have plenty of money to finance comfortable retirements and high-quality healthcare for all citizens, including those at the bottom of the wage ladder.', 73934, 0), (467514, 'Everyone says you''ve got to do a foundation and legal structure to finance social change. What nonsense!', 73935, 0), (467515, 'I know what I don''t know. To this day, I don''t know technology, and I don''t know finance or accounting.', 71262, 0), (467516, 'I hope that there''s a difference between being childish and childlike and that I''m the latter, if you take my meaning. I often sort of wonder. I don''t think I''m a terribly good grown-up; I don''t take responsibility easily or well in many areas of life. Finance and stuff like that, I''m absolutely appalling.', 70840, 0), (467517, 'We need real campaign finance reform to loosen the grip of special interests on politics.', 73810, 0), (467518, 'I went to college at QUT: Queensland University of Technology. I studied for a Bachelors in finance and acting.', 73936, 0), (467519, 'If it isn''t the sheriff, it''s the finance company; I''ve got more attachments on me than a vacuum cleaner.', 26603, 0), (467520, 'As a novelist, I tell stories and people give me money. Then fi